A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, I pretended to be working from home, but was actually editing "Desperate Measures".
If only this damn file could open, I'd be happy (OneDrive is such crap.)
The hacker's voice. I'm in.
He started drilling, the sound was super loud. Great.
Setting the air purifier to its highest setting felt a bit too intense, but I did notice a wood particle smell, so I suppose it's justified. Besides, he opposed wearing a mask. And I do need to take care of myself, don't I?
I really wanted to go back to sleep, but he left only then could I sleep.
Good news is, the fourth chapter has finally been edited!
Chapter 5 is really long and super anxiety-making. Yay, it's so thrilling!
Currently looking for and replacing……➡️ ellipses, a total of 54 in this chapter.
But I still want to insist on this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally excited.
The floor repair worker is using a vacuum cleaner to clean, hopefully this means he is almost done.
He went out (sounding like) cutting something. I glanced at the progress in secret. There's still a lot of work to do :(
Chapter 5 is down to 7 pages. It is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in pretty good shape, mainly just need to adjust the layout, and some minor tweaks to the active voice and concision. But I really need to take a break, have a cup of tea, while that guy is still busy in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. Hopefully, this is a good omen.
The worker who fixed the kitchen floor has left.
He told me that he's going to repair the whole floor, but the landlord is too cheap, only willing to pay for the part in front of the door that's already rotten. I feel much better.
I'm having a cup of tea in the garden, and the air purifier in the kitchen is working hard to purify the air in the room!
